Yes — the fixed v3 version keeps the major upgrades you wanted that are missing in v2.

Main additions in v3:

* Automatic task extraction from logs

  * Example:
    “Navleen’s birthday next Friday, buy skincare set”
    → auto creates task + reminder candidate.

* Dedicated `tasks` table

  * pending/completed
  * due dates
  * priority
  * reminder timestamps
  * auto-schedule flags
  * dedupe protection

* Smart calendar scheduling

  * `/api/tasks/schedule_pending`
  * automatically pushes reminders into Apple Calendar
  * prevents duplicate events

* “Anything pending?” intelligence

  * `/api/ask`
  * now searches pending tasks globally
  * combines follow-ups + reminders + tasks

* Relationship-aware master AI search

  * “What should I gift Navleen?”
  * “Who do I need to reconnect with?”
  * “What did Rahul say about Amsterdam?”
  * uses logs + tasks together

* Agent integration

  * conversational scheduling layer
  * can later become full Jarvis-style planner

* Reminder timing logic

  * priority-based default reminder generation
  * auto reminder timestamps
  * alert-before minutes

* Calendar persistence

  * stores `calendar_href`
  * avoids re-creating same event repeatedly

* Better schema foundation

  * scalable toward:

    * recurring reminders
    * life timelines
    * relationship CRM
    * AI memory graph
    * proactive nudges

Your older v2 app only had:

* logs
* themes
* semantic search
* AI summaries
* ICS alert generation

No real task system existed there. 

The v3 architecture is much closer to the “personal relationship operating system” you were describing.
